         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, bot. Garden ¶ 1. Aug. 1857. ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ I have the honor to transmit to you for the public museum a collection of 25 timber specimens, procured by Mr John Walters ¶  at Sealer's Cove under m...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">57.08.01</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Frederick McCoy</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Archive box 00325, Melbourne Museum, Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne, bot. Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">1. Aug. 1857.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to transmit to you for the public museum a collection of 25 timber specimens, procured by Mr John Walters<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. John Watters, whose journey to Sealers Cove took place 24-29 June 1857 at a cost of £23 15s for travelling expenses and freight for the cases of specimens (Unit 3, p. 214, VPRS 973, PROV).</p>
               </note> at Sealer's Cove under my order. I beg to recommend, that each specimen should be divided into two longitudinally, to allow the moisture to evaporate more freely, and to prevent the splitting of the specimens.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your most obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Prof. M'Coy</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c</p>
         </div>
